Aim
To perform a WHOIS lookup for a target domain and analyze the registrar details, domain owner information,
and expiry date.
Introduction
WHOIS is a protocol used to retrieve registration information about domain names and IP addresses. It
provides details such as registrar information, domain creation date, expiry date, nameservers, and
organization details.
Cybersecurity professionals use WHOIS lookup for domain investigation, reconnaissance, and security
analysis.
Procedure
Step 1: Install WHOIS Tool
Open Kali Linux terminal and install the WHOIS package:
sudo apt install whois -y
Step 2: Verify WHOIS Installation
Check whether WHOIS is installed:
whois --version
Step 3: Perform WHOIS Lookup
Run the WHOIS command for the target domain:
whois www.grace.edu.in
Step 4: Analyze the Information
Observe:
• Registrar details
• Domain owner information
• Creation date
• Expiry date
• Name server details
Implementation
Command Used
whois www.grace.edu.in
Explanation
• whois → WHOIS lookup command
• www.grace.edu.in → Target domain name
Output
Domain Name: grace.edu.in
Registrar: ERNET India
Organization: GRACE COLLEGE OF ENGINEERING
Creation Date: 2024-10-30
Registry Expiry Date: 2034-10-30
Name Server: ns1.dns-parking.com
Result
Thus, the WHOIS lookup was performed successfully and domain registration details were analyzed
